data.title: What Is There to Say by The Chico Hamilton Trio
data.meta_description: What Is There to Say by The Chico Hamilton Trio was written by Vernon Duke and was first performed by Jane Froman & Everett Marshall. The Chico Hamilton Trio released it on the album The Chico Hamilton Trio in 1955. It was covered by Tommy Leonetti, Turtle Island String Quartet, The Red Garland Quintet with John Coltrane and Donald Byrd, The Brian Nova Trio with Buddy Catlett and other artists.
